article.headline: Katherine Harry's career game lifts DePaul past Loyola-Chicago
article.linkText: Harry scores career-high 20 to help DePaul win
article.story:
CHICAGO --  Katherine Harry scored a career-high 20 points and DePaul (No. 24 AP) claimed an 80-48 victory over Loyola-Chicago on Thursday night.

Harry, a sophomore forward, had 12 rebounds while teammates Felicia Chester and Sam Quigley both added 12 points as the Blue Demons (10-1) won their seventh straight game. Chester added eight rebounds.

DePaul overcame poor early shooting to build leads as large as 22 points late in the first half and were up 42-21 at halftime.

Monica Albano scored a game-high 21-points for the host Ramblers (4-4).
